# ${AGENT_DISPLAY_NAME}

> Generated by **Agent SDK Onboarder**.
> Tenant: `${TENANT_ID}` &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp; Entra app: `${CLIENT_ID}` &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp; Provider: `${PROVIDER}`

This folder contains a fully governed wrapper for your agent. Every chat turn
flows through Microsoft Purview content scanning + audit, and emits Agent 365
Observability spans.

```
prompt -> Purview processContent -> [if allowed] -> ${PROVIDER} agent
                                                       v
        Purview processContent on response -> Purview recordActivity (audit)
                                                       v
        return ChatResult (or block reason)
```

## Quick start

```powershell
# 1. one-time setup
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 2. run
python -m uvicorn server:app --host ${SERVER_HOST} --port ${SERVER_PORT}
```

Then open <http://${SERVER_HOST}:${SERVER_PORT}/> and sign in with a tenant user.

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `server.py` | FastAPI app: OAuth, /chat, minimal UI |
| `${AGENT_WRAPPER_MODULE}.py` | Purview governance wrapper (DLP, audit, policy enforcement) |
| `agent_observability.py` | Defensive Agent 365 SDK wrapper (OTel spans) |
| `adapter.py` | Provider-specific downstream call (`${PROVIDER}`) |
| `.env` | Tenant + agent + provider configuration (DO NOT COMMIT) |
| `requirements.txt` | Python dependencies |
| `_onboarding-report.json` | Record of what the onboarder did |

## Verifying it works

| Where | What you should see |
|---|---|
| `audit.log` (in this folder) | One JSONL entry per chat turn |
| Purview portal → DSPM for AI → AI apps | `${AGENT_DISPLAY_NAME}` listed (~10 min after first chat) |
| Microsoft 365 admin center → Agents | (If you opted into Agent 365 blueprint) `${AGENT_DISPLAY_NAME}` listed |
| Server stdout | `agent365 telemetry configured (export=console\|agent365 ingestion)` on startup |

